                  <p class="p">Understand Your Map &amp; Timing</p>
                  <p class="text-wrapper-6">
                    To start, print out the hiking guide and map. If it’s raining, throw them in a Zip-Lock bag. Read
                    over the guide, study the map, and have a good idea of what to expect. I like to know what my next
                    landmark is as I hike. For example, I’ll read the guide and know that say, in a mile, I make a right
                    turn at the junction..
